Ekuma Jeremiah, the young hawker, who was caught on camera in Ajah area of Lagos giving money to inmates in the Correctional Service van, has met with businessman and popular socialite Obi Cubana. The Nation reports Jeremiah was caught on camera in the Ajah area of Lagos last week giving money to inmates in a Nigerian Correctional Service van. In the 7-second video, the hawker is seen carrying a crate of bottled water on his head while giving out some of the money he had made. His gesture earned a widespread commendation from many Nigerians. They applauded him for his love and generosity. - Advertisement - The Nation reports Obi had during an Instagram live interview hosted by Ifedayo Olarinde, aka Daddy Freeze, offered to sponsor the hawker’s tertiary education in any institution of his choice.   PHOTOS: Obi Cubana meets Lagos hawker, restates scholarship…     I’ll change TikTok game in 2022, says Jenni Frank     Mob sets two robber suspects ablaze in Onitsha   To fulfill the promises made, Jeremiah in company of Daddy Freeze, the man who shot the viral video – Rocky and others met with Obi Cubana. Daddy Freeze, in the video shared on Facebook, showed Obi commending Jeremiah for his good gestures. He also applauded Rocky for bringing the hawker into limelight. Daddy Freeze advised that as long as Jeremiah remains serious, and have a good plan for his life, something good would definitely happen to his life and career. Jeremiah while appreciating Daddy Freeze and Obi Cubana, expressed gratitude to God, and also thanked people who God has anointed to uplift him. He promised to remain faithful and do his best as regards his academics.